obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32569)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Appointment of Director and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=32569&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, appoint,--`
  line
  line `(a) A Director of Wild Life Preservation;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(c) such other officers and employees as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) In the performance of his duties and exercise of his powers by or under this Act, the Director shall`
  line `be subject to such general or special directions, as the Central Government may, from time to time, give.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) The officers and other employees appointed under this section shall be required to assist the`
  line Director.]
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (b) omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32570)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of Life Warden and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=32570&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government May, for the`
  line `purpose of this Act, appoint,--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chief Wild Life Warden;`
  line
  line `(b) Wild Life Wardens; ^1***`
  line
  line `^2[(bb) Honorary Wild Life Wardens;]`
  line
  line `(c) such other officers and employees as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) In the performance of his duties and exercise of his powers by or under this Act, the Chief Wild`
  line `Life Warden shall be subject to such general or special directions, as the State Government may from`
  line `time to time, give.`
  line
  line `(3) ^3[The Wild Life Warden, the Honorary Wild Life Warden] and other officers and employees`
  line `appointed under this section shall be subordinate to the Chief Wild Life Warden.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "and" omitted by 44 of 1991, s. 6 (w.e.f. 2-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 2003, s. 5, for clause (bb) (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 44 of 1991, s. 6, for "The Wild Life Warden" (w.e.f. 2-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32590)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=32590&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director may, with the previous approval of the Central Government,`
  line `by order in writing, delegate all or any of his powers and duties under this Act to any officer subordinate`
  line `to him subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Wild Life Warden may, with the previous approval of the State Government, by order`
  line `in writing, delegate all or any of his powers and duties under this Act, except those under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 11, to any officer subordinate to him subject to such conditions, if any, as may`
  line `be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to any general or special direction given or condition imposed by the Director or the Chief`
  line `Wild Life Warden, any person, authorised by the Director or the Chief Wild Life Warden to exercise any`
  line `powers, may exercise those powers in the same manner and to the same effect as if they had been`
  line `conferred on that person directly by this Act and not by way of delegation.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (32591)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Constitution of the National Board for Wild Life.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=32591&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Constitution of the National Board for Wild Life.-- ( (1) The Central Government shall,`
  line `within three months from the date of commencement of the Wild Life (Protection) Amendment Act, 2002`
  line `(16 of 2003), constitute the National Board for Wild Lifeconsisting of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Prime Minister as Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) the Minister in-charge of Forests and Wild Life as Vice-Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(c) three members of Parliament of whom two shall be from the House of the People and one`
  line `from the Council of States;`
  line
  line `^2[(d) Member, NITI Aayog in-charge of Environment, Forest and Climate Change;]`
  line
  line `(e) five persons to represent non-governmental organizations to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(f) ten persons to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst eminent`
  line `conservationists, ecologists and environmentalists;`
  line
  line `(g) the Secretary to the Government of India in-charge of the Ministry or Department of the`
  line `Central Government dealing with Forests and Wild Life;`
  line
  line `(h) the Chief of the Army Staff;`
  line
  line `(i) the Secretary to the Government of India in-charge of the Ministry of Defence;`
  line
  line `(j) the Secretary to the Government of India in-charge of the Ministry of Information and`
  line Broadcasting;
  line
  line `(k) the Secretary to the Government of India in-charge of the Department of Expenditure,`
  line `Ministry of Finance;`
  line
  line `(l) the Secretary to the Government of India, Ministry of Tribal Welfare;`
  line
  line `(m) the Director-General of Forests in the Ministry or Department of the Central Government`
  line `dealing with Forests and Wild Life;`
  line
  line `(n) the Director-General of Tourism, Government of India;`
  line
  line `(o) the Director-General, Indian Council for Forestry Research and Education, Dehradun;`
  line
  line `(p) the Director, Wild Life Institute of India, Dehradun;`
  line
  line `(q) the Director, Zoological Survey of India;`
  line
  line `(r) the Director, Botanical Survey of India;`
  line
  line `(s) the Director, Indian Veterinary Research Institute;`
  line
  line `(t) the Member-Secretary, Central Zoo Authority;`
  line
  line `(u) the Director, National Institute of Oceanography;`
  line
  line `(v) one representative each from ten States and Union territories by rotation, to be nominated by`
  line `the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(w) the Director of Wild Life Preservation who shall be the Member-Secretary of the National`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of the members other than those who are members ex officio, the manner of`
  line `filling vacancies referred to in clauses (e), (f) and (v) of sub-section (1), and the procedure to be followed`
  line `in the discharge of their functions by the members of the National Board shall be such, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) The members (except members ex officio) shall be entitled to receive such allowances in respect`
  line `of expenses incurred in the performance of their duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the office of a`
  line `member of the National Board shall not be deemed to be an office of profit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2003, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2022, s. 4, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 1-4-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_b:
  sectionId (32592)
  sectionNo 5B
  orderNo 7
  title `Standing Committee of the National Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2003, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=32592&sectionno=5B&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[5B. Standing Committee of the National Board.-- (1) The National Board may, in its discretion,`
  line `constitute a Standing Committee for the purpose of exercising such powers and performing such duties as`
  line `may be delegated to the Committee by the National Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Standing Committee shall consist of the Vice-Chairperson, the Member-Secretary, and not`
  line `more than ten members to be nominated by the Vice-Chairperson from amongst the members of the`
  line `National Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The National Board may constitute committees, sub-committees or study groups, as may be`
  line `necessary, from time to time in proper discharge of the functions assigned to it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_c:
  sectionId (32594)
  sectionNo 5C
  orderNo 8
  title `Functions of the National Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2003, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=32594&sectionno=5C&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_5_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[5C. Functions of the National Board.-- (1) It shall be the duty of the National Board to promote the`
  line `conservation and development of wild life and forests by such measures as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, the measures referred to therein`
  line `may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) framing policies and advising the Central Government and the State Governments on the ways`
  line `and means of promoting wild life conservation and effectively controlling poaching and illegal trade`
  line `of wild life and its products;`
  line
  line `(b) making recommendations on the setting up of and management of national parks, sanctuaries`
  line `and other protected areas and on matters relating to restriction of activities in those areas;`
  line
  line `(c) carrying out or causing to be carried but impact assessment of various projects and activities`
  line `on wild life or its habitat;`
  line
  line `(d) reviewing from time to time, the progress in the field of wild life conservation in the country`
  line `and suggesting measures for improvement thereto; and`
  line
  line `(e) preparing and publishing a status report at least once in two years on wild life in the country.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (32595)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 9
  title `Constitution of State Board for Wild Life.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2003, s. 7, for section 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003)..`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=32595&sectionno=6&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Constitution of State Board for Wild Life.-- (1) The State Government shall, within a period of`
  line `six months from the date of commencement of the Wild Life (Protection) Amendment Act, 2002 (16 of`
  line `2003) constitute a State Board for Wild Life consisting of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Minister of the State and in case of the Union territory, either Chief Minister or`
  line `Administrator, as the case may be - Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) the Minister in-charge of Forests and Wild Life - Vice-Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(c) three members of the State Legislature or in the case of a Union territory with Legislature, two`
  line `members of the Legislative Assembly of that Union territory;`
  line
  line `(d) three persons to represent non-governmental organizations dealing with wild life to be`
  line `nominated by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(e) ten persons to be nominated by the State Government from amongst eminent conservationists,`
  line `ecologists and environmentalists including at least two representatives of the Scheduled Tribes;`
  line
  line `(f) the Secretary to the State Government or the Government of the Union territory, as the case`
  line `may be, in-charge of Forests and Wild Life;`
  line
  line `(g) the Officer in-charge of the State Forest Department;`
  line
  line `(h) the Secretary to the State Government, Department of Tribal Welfare;`
  line
  line `(i) the Managing Director, State Tourism Development Corporation;`
  line
  line `(j) an officer of the State Police Department not below the rank of Inspector-General;`
  line
  line `(k) a representative of the Armed Forces not below the rank of a Brigadier to be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government;.`
  line
  line `(l) the Director, Department of Animal Husbandry of the State;`
  line
  line `(m) the Director, Department of Fisheries of the State;`
  line
  line `(n) an officer to be nominated by the Director, Wild Life Preservation;`
  line
  line `(o) a representative of the Wild Life Institute of India, Dehradun;`
  line
  line `(p) a representative of the Botanical Survey of India;`
  line
  line `(q) a representative of the Zoological Survey of India;`
  line
  line `(r) the Chief Wild Life Warden, who shall be the Member-Secretary.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of the members other than those who are members ex officio and the manner of`
  line `filling vacancies referred to in clauses (d) and (e) of sub-section (1) and procedure to be followed shall be`
  line `such, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The member (except members ex officio) shall be entitled to receive such allowances in respect of`
  line `expenses incurred in the performance of their duties as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (73291)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 10
  title `Standing Committee of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2022, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=73291&sectionno=6A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Standing Committee of Board.--(1) The Board may constitute a Standing Committee for the`
  line `purpose of exercising such powers and performing such duties as may be delegated to it by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Standing Committee shall consist of the Vice-Chairperson, the Member-Secretary, and not`
  line `more than ten members, to be nominated by the Vice-Chairperson, from amongst the members of the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(3) The Board or its Standing Committee referred to in sub-section (1) may, constitute committees,`
  line `sub-committees or study groups, as may be necessary, from time-to-time, for proper discharge of the`
  line `functions assigned to it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (32597)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 11
  title `Procedure to be followed by the Board`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=32597&sectionno=7&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall meet at least twice a year at such`
  line `place as the State Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall regulate its own procedure (including the quorum)`
  line
  line `(3) No act or proceeding of the Board shall be invalid merely by reason of the existence of any`
  line `vacancy therein or any defect in the constitution thereof or any irregularity in the procedure of the Board`
  line `not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (32599)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 12
  title `Duties of State Board for Wild Life.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=32599&sectionno=8&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Duties of ^1[State Board for Wild Life]-- It shall be the duty of ^1[State Board for Wild Life] to`
  line `advise the State Government,--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) in the selection and management of areas to be declared as protected areas;]`
  line
  line `^3[(b) in formulation of the policy for protection and conservation of the wild life and specified`
  line plants;]
  line
  line `(c) in any matter relating to the amendment of any Schedule; ^4***`
  line
  line `^5[(cc) in relation to the measures to be taken for harmonising the needs of the tribals and other`
  line `dwellers of the forest with the protection and conservation of wild life; and]`
  line
  line `(d) in any other matter connected with the protection of wild life, which may bereferred to it by`
  line `the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2003, s. 8, for "the Wild Life Advisory Board" (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 44 of 1991, s. 8, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 2-10-1991).`
  line
  line `4. The word "and" omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-10-1991).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (32603)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 13
  title `Prohibition of hunting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=32603&sectionno=9&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Prohibition of hunting.---No person shall hunt any wild animal specified in ^2[Schedules I and`
  line `II] except as provided under section 11 and section 12.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for section 9 (w.e.f. 2-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2022, s. 6, for "Schedules I, II, III and IV" (w.e.f. 1-4-2023).`
