  string
  line `[10. Maintenance of records of wild animals killed or captured.]---Omitted by the Wild Life`
  line `(Protection) Amendment Act, 1991 (44 of 1991), s. 10 (w.e.f. 2-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (32606)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 15
  title `Hunting of wild animals to be permitted in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=32606&sectionno=11&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force and subject to the provisions of Chapter IV,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Wild Life Warden may, if he is satisfied that any wild animal specified in Schedule`
  line `I has become dangerous to human life or is so disabled or diseased as to be beyond recovery, by`
  line `Order in writing and stating the reasons therefor, permit any person to hunt such animal or cause such`
  line `animal to be hunted;`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that no wild animal shall be ordered to be killed unless the Chief Wild Life Warden is`
  line `satisfied that such animal cannot be captured, tranquilised or translocated:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such captured animal shall be kept in captivity unless the Chief Wild Life`
  line `Warden is satisfied that such animal cannot be rehabilitated in the wild and the reasons for the same`
  line `are recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of clause (a), the process of capture or translocation, as the case`
  line `may be, of such animal shall be made in such manner as to cause minimum trauma to the said animal]`
  line
  line `(b) the Chief Wild Life Warden or the authorised officer may, if he is satisfied that any wild`
  line `animal specified in Schedule II, ^2***, has become dangerous to human life or to property (including`
  line `standing crops on any land) or is so disabled or diseased as to be beyond recovery, by order in writing and stating the reasons therefor, permit any person to hunt ^3[such animal`
  line `or group of animals in a specified area or cause such animal or group of animals in that specified area`
  line `to be hunted].`
  line
  line `(2) The killing or wounding in good faith of any wild animal in defence of oneself or of any other`
  line `person shall not be an offence:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall exonerate any person who, when such defence becomes`
  line `necessary, was committing any act in contravention of any provision of this Act or any rule or order made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(3) Amy wild animal killed or wounded in defence of any person shall be Government property.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2003, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line
  line `2. The words and figures "Schedule III, or Schedule IV" omitted by Act 18 of 2022, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s.9, ibid., for "such animal or cause such animal to be hunted" (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (32607)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 16
  title `Grant of permit for special purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579&sectionId=32607&sectionno=12&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00007_197253_1517807324579
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained elsewhere in this`
  line `Act, it shall be lawful for the Chief Wild Life Warden, to grant^1***a permit, by an order in writing stating`
  line `the reasons therefor, to any person, on payment of such fee as may be prescribed, which shall entitle the`
  line `holder of such permit to hunt subject to such conditions as may be specified therein, any wild animal`
  line `specified in such permit, for the purpose of,--`
  line
  line `(a) education;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) scientific research;`
  line
  line `(bb) scientific management.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of clause (bb), the expression, "scientific management" means--`
  line
  line `(i) translocation of any wild animals to an alternative suitable habitat; or`
  line
  line `(ii) population management of wildlife, without killing or poisoning or destroying any wild`
  line animals;]
  line
  line `^3[(c) collection of specimens--`
  line
  line `(i) for recognised zoos subject to the permission under section 38-I; or`
  line
  line `(ii) for museums and similar institutions;`
  line
  line `(d) derivation, collection or preparation of snake-venom for the manufacture of life-saving`
  line `drugs:]`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that no such permit shall be granted--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of any wild animal specified in Schedule I, except with the previous permission`
  line `of the Central Government, and`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of any other wild animal, except with the previous permission of the State`
  line Government;]
  line
  line `(d) derivation, collection or preparation of snake-venom for the manufacture of life-saving`
  line `drugs:]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words ", with the previous permission of the State Government" omitted by Act 23 of 1982, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21-5-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 21-5-1982).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 44 of 1991, s. 11, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 2-10-1991).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 1982, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21-5-1982).`
